Inspect a Python/NVIDIA environment, enumerate wheels that actually exist on the official PyTorch
indexes, and recommend only reviewed configurations whose driver, ABI, platform, and GPU
compatibility can be established statically.

Usage: torch-check [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  inspect      Display detected OS, Python, NVIDIA, GPU, glibc, and Toolkit details
  recommend    Select the highest-ranked reviewed, statically compatible configuration
  candidates   List candidates by review and compatibility stage
  explain      Explain every check for one exact PyTorch/CUDA pair
  verify       Import installed PyTorch and execute bounded runtime checks
  completions  Generate a shell completion script
  man          Generate the roff man page on stdout
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --python <PATH>
          Python interpreter to inspect, verify, and use in generated commands

      --gpu <INDEX>
          Physical nvidia-smi GPU indices to consider (comma-separated). Empty means every device

      --format <FORMAT>
          Human-readable or stable machine-readable output
          
          [default: human]
          [possible values: human, json]

      --refresh
          Bypass a fresh wheel-index cache

      --offline
          Never access the network; require a complete cached index

      --cache-dir <PATH>
          Override the platform cache directory

      --redact
          Remove GPU UUIDs and local interpreter paths from output

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
